# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Buttons Bebe / Hermes agent — .gitignore
#
# HARD RULE: secrets and customer data must NEVER be committed.
# The KB Markdown (kb/**) and the application source code ARE tracked.
# Everything below is excluded.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# --- Secrets / credentials (config.json holds the encrypted Gorgias API key,
#     webhook secret_token, and Telegram bot token — never commit it) ---
config.json
config.local.json
.env
.env.*
*.env
secrets.json
*.pem
*.key
# OS / server key material referenced from outside the repo
/etc/*

# --- Operational data stores (built by other tasks) ---
# feedback.db (drafts / replies / comparisons) — contains customer PII
*.db
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3
*.db-journal
*.db-wal
*.db-shm

# --- Exports of real tickets/messages (PII: names, emails, orders) ---
# Ignore the whole exports/ dir — ALL of it is derived real-ticket data (csv,
# json, logs, .zip bundles, state markers). None of it belongs in git.
exports/

# --- Per-ticket context snapshots fetched from Gorgias (raw PII) ---
ticket_contexts/

# --- Backups (Task 17): pg dumps, sqlite snapshots, KB git bundles ---
# Operational data stores — convenience/DR copies, never belong in git.
# (Re-asserted at the very bottom so no !kb rule can re-include anything here.)
backups/

# --- Webhook capture / logs ---
webhook_events.jsonl
*.jsonl
*.log
webhooks.log

# --- Python ---
.venv/
venv/
env/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd
*.egg-info/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/

# --- Editor / OS noise ---
.DS_Store
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*~

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Explicitly KEEP the knowledge base and its scaffolding.
# (Negations below override the broad rules above where they would conflict.)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
!kb/
!kb/**/.gitkeep
!kb/**/*.md

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Final hard exclusion — after the kb negations above — so nothing under
# backups/ (e.g. a kb-*.bundle) can ever be re-included by a !kb/** rule.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
backups/

# editor/script backups
*.bak
*.bak-*
